    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-14T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-14T21:00:00-05:00" n="1090"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1090">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A PW/10–2744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-14T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 14, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3878. American Interests, China. Reurtel 7135, October 27, and 6870, October
                        16.<note n="34" xml:id="d1090fn34">Neither printed.</note> In view of
                    extraordinary rise in prices at Shanghai, request Swiss to ask their Legation in
                    Japan whether a more favorable basis may be arranged for obtaining local
                    currency in that city. The doubling or tripling of commodity prices from June to
                    October makes the rate of 9.18 Swiss francs for 100 CRB dollars (ReLegs 7051,
                    October 24,<note n="35" xml:id="d1090fn35">Not printed; but for summary, see
                        footnote 9, <ref target="#pg_1056">p. 1056</ref>.</note> and 3583, June 5)
                    at least as inequitable as was the former rate of exchange. Department
                    appreciates action by Gorgé in negotiating present basis for obtaining Chinese
                    Reserve Bank dollars as already stated (ReDeptel 3482, October 10) and hopes he
                    will be able to make further advantageous arrangements.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
